com.facebook.buck.core.model

Interface UnconfiguredBuildTargetView

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Comparable<UnconfiguredBuildTargetView>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    ImmutableUnconfiguredBuildTargetView

    @ThreadSafe
public interface UnconfiguredBuildTargetView
extends Comparable<UnconfiguredBuildTargetView>
    Represents a view over UnconfiguredBuildTarget.

    This view adds runtime context information to UnconfiguredBuildTarget, like absolute cell path where build target belongs to. Because of that, this class should not be used as a long-living data class with the lifetime exceeding the lifetime of running command.

    This class represents a legacy data structure. In most of the cases you will want to use UnconfiguredBuildTarget directly.

      • getCell

        CanonicalCellName getCell()
        The canonical name of the cell specified in the build target.

        Note that this name can be different from the name specified on the name. See CellPathResolver.getCanonicalCellName(java.nio.file.Path) for more information.

      • getCellPath

        Path getCellPath()
        The path to the root of the cell where this build target is used.

        Note that the same build target name can reference different build targets when used in different cells. For example, given a target name external_cell//lib:target, for a cell that maps external_cell to a cell with location /cells/cell_a, this build target would point to a target //lib:target in the /cells/cell_a cell (defined in a build file located in /cells/cell_a/lib folder. If another cell uses the same build target name, but points external_cell to a different cell, say /cells/cell_b, then this build target refers to a target //lib:target in the /cells/cell_b cell.

      • getBaseName

        String getBaseName()
        Part of build target name the colon excluding cell name.

        For example, for cell//third_party/java/guava:guava this returns //third_party/java/guava.
